Sentencas: This paper uses finite element method (FEM) to predict the residual stress and plastic strain in the brazed joint of sealing foil-to-window frame in bonded compliant seal (BCS) design in a planar solid oxide fuel cell (PSOFC).
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of window frame material type, sealing foil thickness, filler metal thickness and window frame thickness on residual stress and plastic strain are discussed.
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Large residual stress is generated in the joint, and the stress and strain are concentrated around the fillet.
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: It is proved that the BCS design can mitigate and trap some residual stress by plastic deformation within the sealing foil.
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The residual stress and the ability of trapping stress of sealing foil are affected by window frame material and structure thickness.
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Based on the comprehensive considerations of the impact of residual stress and plastic strain, Alloy 625 as a window frame material is found to be better than Haynes 214, Hastelloy X and SUS 316L. The optimum thickness of sealing foil and filler metal BNi2 are found to be 150 mu m and 75 mu m, respectively.
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The residual stress and plastic strain are increased with the increase of window frame thickness.
Titulo: Residual stress and plastic strain analysis in the brazed joint of bonded compliant seal design in planar solid oxide fuel cell
